SIMPLE: jurat
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Jurat
<hw>Ju"rat</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prov. F.
<ets>jurat</ets>, fr. L. <ets>juratus</ets> sworn, <ets>p. p.</ets> of
<ets>jurare</ets> to swear. See <er>Jury</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A person under oath; specifically, an officer of the
nature of an alderman, in certain municipal corporations in
England.</def> <rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The memorandum or certificate at
the end of an affidavit, or a bill or answer in chancery, showing when,
before whom, and (in English practice), where, it was sworn or
affirmed.</def> <rj><au>Wharton. Bouvier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Juratory</ent>⟦br⟧
